Knit refers to the process of creating fabric by interlocking loops of yarn or thread using two or more needles or knitting hooks. The term "knit" can refer to the finished product as well as the act of creating it.

Wrinkle refers to the uneven surface or texture of fabric that results from the way it was made or finished.

Raw edge refers to fabric with unfinished edges that have not been hemmed or otherwise treated.

Crochet is a technique for creating fabric by pulling loops of yarn through previous stitches using a crochet hook.</s>
